Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} or #wok{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%grams} and stir-fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a #bowl{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{1}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Slice widthways into pieces about 1/2cm thick.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Quarter and peel the @onion{1}, then separate the layers. Trim the @green beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds.

Pop the (now empty) pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} if needed (no need to clean).

Once hot, add the carrot, onion and beans and stir-fry until softened, ~{6-7%minutes}.

While the veg fries, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%grams} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

In a small bowl, mix together the @mango chutney{40%grams}, @bulgogi sauce{75%grams}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} and @water{1%tbsp} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts). Set aside your sticky sauce.

Stir the garlic into the veg and fry until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

Stir in the sticky sauce, then stir through the cooked chicken and noodles.

Toss to coat everything in the sauce, stirring frequently until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{splash} if it's a little dry.

When ready, share the chicken stir-fry between your bowls. Enjoy!